The Chronicle Chronicle Reporter NINETEEN more Covid-19 deaths and 300 new cases were recorded yesterday in the country. The Ministry of Health and Child Care said as of yesterday the country had recorded 32 304 cases, 23 687 recoveries and 1 122 deaths. 205 people were in hospitals across the country suffering from the virus. A total of 3 666 tests were done and the positivity rate stood at 8,6percent. 274 new recoveries were recorded and the national recovery rate now stands at 72,2percent. “As of January 26, 2021at 3pm, there were 205 hospitalised, 127 mild to moderate cases, 65 severe, and 13 in intensive care unit,” reads an update from the Ministry of Health and Child Care